VIII. OEo Almam.

It never through my mind had passed, The time would e'er be o’er,

And I on thee should look my last,

And thou shouldst smile no more.

And still upon that face I look, And think ‘t will smile again 3

And still the thought I will not brook‚ That. Ι must look in vain!
